value: Central Siberia from west of the upper Yenisey River east to Anadyrland, Koryakland, and Kamchatka, north to about the northern limit of the taiga, south to the Russian Altai, Tannu Tuva, Lake Baykal, Transbaicalia, Amurland, Sakha- lin, and Kuril Islands.
